
[1]penitency

   PENITENCY, n. [L. poenitentia, from poeniteo, from poena, pain,
   punishment. See Pain.] Repentance; pain; sorrow or grief of heart for
   sins or offenses; contrition. Real penitence springs from a conviction
   of guilt and ingratitude to God, and is followed by amendment of life.
